<div id="review_1998125268" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1998125268" />
    <a title="Luca Prosperi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41140889-luca-prosperi"><img alt="Luca Prosperi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1426150943p2/41140889.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1998125268?book_show_action=true">Nov 29, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Luca Prosperi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Luca Prosperi" href="/user/show/41140889-luca-prosperi">Luca Prosperi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1998125268" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6336634886811032400">When I finished Barney&apos;s Version, I am not ashamed to say, I had a couple of tears on my cheeks. It was like saying farewell to an old friend with whom I wen through the imperfections, the moments of happiness and doom, of a long life. I will miss you Barney. I will miss your sense of humour, your political incorrectness, and the depth of your often misunderstood feelings. I will miss and envy your incommensurate love for Miriam, as much as your despise for The Second Mrs. P., which I learned to</span>
  <span id="freeText6336634886811032400" style="display:none">When I finished Barney's Version, I am not ashamed to say, I had a couple of tears on my cheeks. It was like saying farewell to an old friend with whom I wen through the imperfections, the moments of happiness and doom, of a long life. I will miss you Barney. I will miss your sense of humour, your political incorrectness, and the depth of your often misunderstood feelings. I will miss and envy your incommensurate love for Miriam, as much as your despise for The Second Mrs. P., which I learned to hate with all my heart and to whom I wish a long and miserable old age lost in hundreds of kilos of fat and loneliness. You have been a dear friend, and I believed you from the very beginning. <br /><br />As you said before your brain began to shrink, "life was absurd, and nobody ever truly understood anybody else.”</span>
