<div id="review_2811309252" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2811309252" />
    <a title="Melissa George" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70420410-melissa-george"><img alt="Melissa George" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1515262060p2/70420410.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2811309252?book_show_action=true">Aug 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melissa George" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melissa George" href="/user/show/70420410-melissa-george">Melissa George</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2811309252" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15227970665190196941">Barney&apos;s Version is the autobiography of Barney Parnofksy, a Montreal Jew coming of age in the 1950s. It opens on his carefree and spirited days in Paris in the late 1950s where he meets his best friend Boogie and his first wife, Clara, then follows the founding of his trashy TV production company Totally Unnecessary Productions, and his 3 tumultuous marriages. At the centre of Barney&apos;s life story is the mysterious disappearance of his best friend, Boogie. When Boogie disappears from Barney&apos;s co</span>
  <span id="freeText15227970665190196941" style="display:none">Barney's Version is the autobiography of Barney Parnofksy, a Montreal Jew coming of age in the 1950s. It opens on his carefree and spirited days in Paris in the late 1950s where he meets his best friend Boogie and his first wife, Clara, then follows the founding of his trashy TV production company Totally Unnecessary Productions, and his 3 tumultuous marriages. At the centre of Barney's life story is the mysterious disappearance of his best friend, Boogie. When Boogie disappears from Barney's cottage property after Barney catches him in bed with the Second Mrs. Panofsky, Barney is charged and subsequently tried for Boogie's murder. <br /><br />Told from the point of view of an increasingly unreliable narrator, readers are treated to a story of a man who is cantankerous, loving, foolish and funny. Barney frequently misremembers events and dates in his lifetime, as well as general information that he once knew. Readers are left wondering how much of Barney's story is true, and most importantly: did Boogie really go for a swim and disappear without a trace, or did Barney's notorious temper get the best of him? </span>
  <a data-text-id="15227970665190196941" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


