    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_332265233" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/332265233" />
    <a title="Laima" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7869613-laima"><img alt="Laima" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1605666912p2/7869613.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/332265233?book_show_action=true">May 18, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laima" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laima" href="/user/show/7869613-laima">Laima</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer332265233" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1099382263745340716">Let me start by saying that Mordecai Richler is not my type of author. I think of him as a writing snob with an aloof style utilizing quotes and phrases or words that, honestly, often shoot way above my head. It may simply come from the fact that I don&apos;t feel that I share much in common with him - not Jewish, didn&apos;t grow up in Montreal.<br/><br/>I did read his novel The Apprenticeship of Duddy Kravitz and although it wasn&apos;t a book I would say I loved, I did find it interesting with something worth saying </span>
  <span id="freeText1099382263745340716" style="display:none">Let me start by saying that Mordecai Richler is not my type of author. I think of him as a writing snob with an aloof style utilizing quotes and phrases or words that, honestly, often shoot way above my head. It may simply come from the fact that I don't feel that I share much in common with him - not Jewish, didn't grow up in Montreal.<br /><br />I did read his novel The Apprenticeship of Duddy Kravitz and although it wasn't a book I would say I loved, I did find it interesting with something worth saying - in other words, it had a message for me.<br /><br />I'm glad I managed to read this entire book, although, I believe it will probably make a better movie than book (not something I've ever said before). I didn't really start laughing out loud until I got to Miriam's section of the novel and was caught laughing out loud several times. I'm also glad that he didn't leave me hanging with regards to whether Barney was a murderer or not - I, like Kate, believed he was innocent throughout the entire story - no matter what the evidence indicated.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="1099382263745340716" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

