    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_857586168" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/857586168" />
    <a title="Evelyn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19089056-evelyn"><img alt="Evelyn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1437415588p2/19089056.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/857586168?book_show_action=true">May 07, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Evelyn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Evelyn" href="/user/show/19089056-evelyn">Evelyn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780676971743" href="/book/show/907804.Barney_s_Version">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer857586168" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12100237523553194941">I thoroughly enjoyed the satire, sarcasm, and humour in this story. Mordecai Richler is a writer who has a way with words and phrases. He tosses in references to literature, politics, sports, movies and exotic locations like no one else. Some of the fun in the reading was challenging myself to recognize and remember the references made. I will admit to googling several of the French phrases scattered throughout- the story is mainly set in Montreal, Quebec, Canada.<br/>Barney is writing his memoir and</span>
  <span id="freeText12100237523553194941" style="display:none">I thoroughly enjoyed the satire, sarcasm, and humour in this story. Mordecai Richler is a writer who has a way with words and phrases. He tosses in references to literature, politics, sports, movies and exotic locations like no one else. Some of the fun in the reading was challenging myself to recognize and remember the references made. I will admit to googling several of the French phrases scattered throughout- the story is mainly set in Montreal, Quebec, Canada.<br />Barney is writing his memoir and loosely divides it into three parts, one for each of his wives. He is beginning to show signs of Alzheimer's and this comes through in his writing. One of his sons has been assigned the job of fact checking and this is accomplished with footnotes scattered throughout. Many of these footnotes add to the humour.<br />This is a book I will definitely re-read at some future time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12100237523553194941" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


